docs.abstract: The club’s green jackets — awarded to its members and Masters winners — are not supposed to leave its grounds. A rare few have, becoming an expensive holy grail for memorabilia collectors.
docs.snippet: The club’s green jackets — awarded to its members and Masters winners — are not supposed to leave its grounds. A rare few have, becoming an expensive holy grail for memorabilia collectors.
docs.lead_paragraph: AUGUSTA, Ga. — Christopher O’Brien is not a member of Augusta National Golf Club, much less a Masters champion. He once played the course “well enough to enjoy it, not well enough to brag about it.”

headline.main: Augusta’s Green Jackets: For Winners, Members (and Buyers) Only

docs.abstract: Bieber, a right-hander for Cleveland, led all major league pitchers in several statistical categories, and Bauer, a right-hander for Cincinnati, wasn’t far behind.
docs.snippet: Bieber, a right-hander for Cleveland, led all major league pitchers in several statistical categories, and Bauer, a right-hander for Cincinnati, wasn’t far behind.
docs.lead_paragraph: Shane Bieber still keeps a screenshot in his cellphone of a text message exchange he had earlier this year with Trevor Bauer, a former teammate in Cleveland whose locker was next to his. Although the Indians traded Bauer to the Cincinnati Reds midway through the 2019 season, the two starting pitchers still stay in frequent touch. And before the 2020 season began, they had similar betting odds to win the Cy Young Awards in their leagues.

headline.main: Shane Bieber and Trevor Bauer Win Cy Young Awards
headline.print_headline: Bieber (a Walk-on) and Bauer (a Free Agent) Win the Cy Young Awards

docs.abstract: A plan to honor Lee Elder, the first Black golfer to compete in the Masters, highlights the glacial pace of change at the club that hosts golf’s marquee event.
docs.snippet: A plan to honor Lee Elder, the first Black golfer to compete in the Masters, highlights the glacial pace of change at the club that hosts golf’s marquee event.
docs.lead_paragraph: The coronavirus pandemic has silenced the Masters Tournament’s resonant roars. It has erased the par-3 contest, drained the color from the wintering azaleas and brought brisk north winds into play for the first time. This week’s tournament, rescheduled from the first major of the year to the last and stripped down to better safeguard the participants from the virus, is happening in one kind of bubble.

headline.main: At Augusta National, Not Talking About Race Is Tradition
headline.print_headline: A Storied Course Comes Late to the Conversation

docs.abstract: Injuries, fatigue and concern are already mounting amid an unforgiving schedule. But for Europe’s top teams, the worst is still to come.
docs.snippet: Injuries, fatigue and concern are already mounting amid an unforgiving schedule. But for Europe’s top teams, the worst is still to come.
docs.lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, England — For a moment, it looked as if Jürgen Klopp was taking issue with Pep Guardiola. Klopp, the Liverpool manager, had sought out Guardiola, his Manchester City counterpart, as soon as the final whistle had blown on their teams’ draw on Sunday. Klopp pulled Guardiola in close, and then swept his arm out across the field, gesticulating at two sets of players heaving with exhaustion, his face serious and his brow furrowed.

headline.main: Stars in a Slog: The Premier League Grind Will Only Get Worse
headline.print_headline: As the Premier League Grinds On, the Slog Will Only Get Worse

docs.abstract: Brown, the star receiver with a checkered past on and off the field, made his debut with the Buccaneers amid questions around his comeback.
docs.snippet: Brown, the star receiver with a checkered past on and off the field, made his debut with the Buccaneers amid questions around his comeback.
docs.lead_paragraph: The matchup had been anticipated all season: Tom Brady and Drew Brees, two sure-shot Hall of Fame quarterbacks nearing the ends of their careers, facing off in prime time on Sunday. The fact that their teams, the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and the New Orleans Saints, are battling for control of the N.F.C. South only raised the stakes.

headline.main: Tom Brady and the Buccaneers Were Blown Out. Was It an Antonio Brown Curse?
headline.print_headline: Reaching Out to a Troubled Player in a Team’s Time of Need

docs.abstract: The politicization of the ceremonial visit to the Rose Garden by champions is one sign the presidential connection to sports is fraught, maybe inalterably.
docs.snippet: The politicization of the ceremonial visit to the Rose Garden by champions is one sign the presidential connection to sports is fraught, maybe inalterably.
docs.lead_paragraph: Awe and tension filled the air on that sunny afternoon in the Rose Garden four years ago this week. I could feel it, and so could everyone else on hand: The sense of celebration mixed with a gnawing worry for the future.

headline.main: Even With a New President, Sports at the White House Won’t Be the Same
headline.print_headline: Championships Come to Keep Score of a Deepening Divide

docs.abstract: Velazquez, a Hall of Famer, said getting to ride Authentic during this difficult year was “a gift from God.”

docs.lead_paragraph: John Velazquez climbed aboard Authentic on Saturday afternoon with confidence as well as determination to make a vision come true. His mother-in-law told him she had a good feeling about the $6 million Breeders’ Cup Classic. He and his colt, she told him, were going to win a race that had eluded him 19 times before.

headline.main: Authentic Gets ‘Emotional’ Breeders’ Cup Win for John Velazquez
headline.print_headline: Breeders’ Cup Classic Goes Just as Envisioned

docs.abstract: There will always be critics of a soccer super league, those who say the hurdles are too high, that it could never work. Except, of course, that one time when it did.

docs.lead_paragraph: At first glance, the three men sitting around a table in the Embajadores restaurant in downtown Bogotá made unlikely companions. True, they were all roughly the same age, in their mid- to late-20s. And, as they traded tales of adventure, their accents would have given away that all three were Argentines, a long way from home.

headline.main: The Lessons of the Pirate League
headline.print_headline: A Super League Can’t Work, Until It Does

docs.abstract: For years, Los Angeles’s players have borne the burden of a title drought. The unusual circumstances of their World Series win won’t dim the joy and relief that come with the long-awaited championship.
docs.snippet: For years, Los Angeles’s players have borne the burden of a title drought. The unusual circumstances of their World Series win won’t dim the joy and relief that come with the long-awaited championship.
docs.lead_paragraph: ARLINGTON, Texas — At the very end, 2020 did what it does best, intruding on joy with an unwelcome risk-or-reward calculation. Justin Turner, part of the soul of the Los Angeles Dodgers, learned that he had tested positive for the coronavirus during the World Series clincher on Tuesday night at Globe Life Field. Then he defied orders from Major League Baseball security and celebrated on the field with teammates and family members, at times without wearing a mask.

headline.main: After a Dampened Celebration, Enduring Glory Still Awaits the Dodgers
